author: @MsIHaveAVoice
text:
This is an GREAT example of what happens when the girls choose their own groups... Twice Team seriously need to start showing us more of the girls dynamics than the ships they rely on. When Tzuyu said she would go shopping, Momo offered to go straight away. I would ❤to see more of this relationship but, they NEVER show it - super cute!! Chae with Momo &/or Sana (Chae become the eldest when she's with them🤣), Dahyun with Nayeon &/or Jihyo (these 3 are so similar & I'm bored of them pairing Jeon) as well as the Mina and Jihyo dynamic - I feel like there's a lot of banter!

I will not go into the 'how and why' the Twice Team👿 has manipulated the fandom by rarely showing these dynamics - just know that they have and I'm highlighting it so it can end!

I think this would be considered NEW, cute and super entertaining. Plus, if you pair the girls with the ones they're most comfortable with, you would get them talking and interacting more which means we have more to play with in post-production and therefore, more entertaining to the fans - we might even hear Mina speak😮. Authentic will ALWAYS be better!🥰

Add a breath of fresh air to 9 year old tedious and boring formular😴. This includes M/V, which means Twice Team👿 will actually have to come up with original concepts!

FYI - Twice Team👿, on my subtitles they mislabelled Momo as Mina near the end!

author: @justdoyourthing1419
text:
First time I saw them in discord and of course it's about food 😂
Correct me if I'm wrong but 230,000 KRW without meat for supermarket food is quite a lot and not economical spending. If I remember correctly, alcohol, ramen and instant rice are not expensive at all in Korea. 

The dynamics of the group is also funny. Jeongyeon and Jihyo are like parents scolding the irresponsible kids. Dahyun, Mina and Nayeon are in the middle, politely smiling or munching on snacks, trying to keep the harmony. Sana and Tzuyu are the chaotic kids who act according to their feelings and ease the criticism by being cute. Momo and Chaeyoung are the rebellious kids who talk back, justifying their purchases 😂
